\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Fynbos (fine bush) in south africa. Included among the plants o fthe fynbos is a flower called watsonia, a member of the lily family. Like its relative the gladiolus, it has a sizable corm, or bubl, which in the case of watsonia is edible. When fynbos vegetation is deliberatly burned off, watsonia grows back with its density per acre increased five to ten times. It seems the occupants of the region had disocvered this fact.}
