\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Dense mats of sedge called purple nut grass were exposed. The sedge mats were ten feet wide, and every ten-square-foot section could produce an incredible 21k tubers. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The plant collectors at wadi kubbaniya had learned that during october and november the nut grass tubers were small and tender; by february and march they had grown larer and harder and were filled with bitter alkaloids. Even these mature tubers, however, could be rendered edible by grinding them on stones and roasting them. }
