\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The bedrock was pitted with sinkholes and became watering places, crucial landmarks in a world with only ten inches of rain. Broadlief trees. Sand dunes supported ricinodendron trees whose nuts supplied the kung people with half their plant food. Areas of hardpan supported commiphora plants, the preferred food of the beetles whose pupae the kung converted into poison for their arrows.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Called the magic n/um.}
