\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 While many tribes had enemies for neighbors, there was one person who could travel widely without fear of death: the sacred messenger. The messenger might, for example, be carrying the red-painted forearm bone of a deceased relative,. Owing to his sacred mission, the meessenger could not be harmed. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Aborigines did not believe there was such a thing as inevitable natural death. Death resulted either from homicide or witchcraft.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Breath is the difference between life and death. The wind is breath.  Sacred.}
